      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SERINDA (3) ran a solid race first up at Sale when well supported, boxing on solidly for third there with improvement to come. This doesn't look any harder and with natural improvement and fitness she can get the job done. JACKIE'S MAID (1) won easily first up at Kyneton, coming from well back to score impressively. Stringing two together has been a bit tricky but she has to be respected. QUEEN AMANJENA (2) ran well fresh at Caulfield Heath behind a handy mare in Torsheen, boxing on for third in a field of six. This is easier and she did win in this grade before a spell. ICHIBERU (5) just found one better last time and has minor claims again.",
